article.headline: Denver 81, Montana State 79
article.story: BOZEMAN (AP) -- Erik Benzel scored 28 points, including two free throws with less than a minute remaining, as the University of Denver beat Montana State 81-79 Saturday. Montana State (3-5) had a chance to take the lead, but Frank Brown missed a 3-pointer with 7 seconds left. Brett Starkey, who had 13 points for Denver (4-5), hit one of two free throws with 1.2 seconds remaining. The Bobcats trailed 67-60 after Benzel's 3-pointer with 9 minutes left, but Montana State went on a 14-7 run to tie the game at 74 on a Calvin Ento lay-up with 3:10 left. The Bobcats took a 79-78 lead on Jason Erickson's free throw with 1:25 remaining. Ento fouled Benzel with 59.7 seconds on the clock and he hit both free throws. Erickson led Montana State with 19 points. Nick Dissly added 17, Ento had 14 and Danny Faaborg had 13. Yemi Nicholson had 10 for the Pioneers.
